  {
    "client_msg_id": "da08574a-4159-47cc-8ff4-8717efc87e5c",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "<@UJBAJNFLK> I feel you on the \"using the web\" argument. The problem is that there still isn't a quick way to easily make malleable, cross-platform UI without a lot of hassle. We used Ohm as our PEG because we hoped to make a Smalltalk version of the system at some point, but as you know Morphic is too heavy (and undocumented) a beast to get modern-capable UIs running. I'm hopeful for Bloc and that might have been another target down the road.",
    "user": "U01A0KANUUU",
    "ts": "1634729530.109000",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
      "avatar_hash": "gca7b3cd16bf",
      "image_72": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/ca7b3cd16bf67a61acaf224e2219929c.jpg?s=72&d=https%3A%2F%2Fa.slack-edge.com%2Fdf10d%2Fimg%2Favatars%2Fava_0001-72.png",
      "first_name": "",
      "real_name": "Eric Gade",
      "display_name": "Eric Gade",
      "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
      "name": "eric.gade",
      "is_restricted": false,
      "is_ultra_restricted": false
    },
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "J2Ym",
        "elements": [
